==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sample
<hw>Sam"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sample</ets>, <ets>asaumple</ets>, OF. <ets>essample</ets>,
<ets>example</ets>, fr. L. <ets>exemplum</ets>. See <er>Example</er>,
and cf. <er>Ensample</er>, <er>Sampler</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Example; pattern.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <au>Spenser.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>sample</xex> to the youngest.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thus he concludes, and every hardy knight⟦br⟧
His <qex>sample</qex> followed.</q> <rj><qau>Fairfax.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A part of anything presented for inspection, or
shown as evidence of the quality of the whole; a specimen; <as>as, goods
are often purchased by <ex>samples</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I design this but for a <qex>sample</qex> of what I hope more
fully to discuss.</q> <rj><qau>Woodward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Specimen; example. See
<er>Specimen</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sample</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sample
<hw>Sam"ple</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make or show
something similar to; to match.</def> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To take or to test a sample or samples of; <as>as,
to <ex>sample</ex> sugar, teas, wools, cloths</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sampler</ent>⟦br⟧
